The three-day symposium is being attended by 200 participants
from the United States, Canada, the United Kingdom, Mexico, Japan,
Singapore, Malaysia, Egypt, India, Australia and Indonesia.

The companies with the 10 largest turnovers were: Hualon-Teijran;
Ever Fortune; Mosel Vitelic; Formosa Plastic; China Petrochemical
Development; Shinkong Synthetic Fibers; United Micro Electronics;
Formosa Chemical and Fiber; Nan Ya Plastic; and ACER.
